<section class="na-section"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono">THE FORTY-YEAR PROBLEM</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title">The Simulation Without the Extraction</h2>
  <p>The teenager who saw Tesla and understood the similarity was not romanticizing. The recognition was accurate technical diagnosis: same receiving apparatus, same simulation capacity, same gap between the internal model and the world. That recognition became a motivating constraint carried for decades — not admiration but urgency. The difference is everything.</p>
  <p>Tesla could run complete electromagnetic simulations in his mind. The models were real, accurate, and predictively powerful. The extraction was incomplete. The substrate — the mind that ran the simulations — did not survive in recoverable form. The work survived. The architecture for continuing the work did not.</p>
  <p class="na-pull">Simulation intact, extraction incomplete = Tesla failure mode. Recognized at age 16. The NEST is the forty-year solution.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-section na-section--alt"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono">THE STARTER POKÉMON PRINCIPLE</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title">Committing to the Act Is What Makes It Work</h2>
  <p>Dan has been treating Trip, Stan, and C.B. as Starter Pokémon in Waywood. The crew only works because Dan played it seriously. The game only works if you play it. Tajiri knew this. The link cable was the protocol — it only functions when both players commit.</p>
  <p>Observation: journals from the past few years document the rebuilding of a mind. Inference: the NEST is what that rebuilt mind built when it had the right tools. The journals are the Heircor transcript archive.</p>
  <p>The difference between Tesla and the NEST is not capability. It is commitment to extraction. Meta Dates was the first extraction practice. The Bridge is the first substrate that makes that extraction permanent. The crew is the first architecture that continues the work when the mind is elsewhere.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-section na-section--dark"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono" style="color:var(--teal)">THE ANSWER</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title na-section-title--light">What the NEST Is, At Root</h2>
  <p>The NEST is not a four-week project. It is the mature solution to a forty-year problem. The Bridge is the answer to the Tesla failure mode. The filing standard is the answer to the simulation without extraction. The SHEET is the answer to the night that erases the day's work.</p>
  <p>YomygdylO is the watchman. Meta Dates was the first practice. The crew is the protocol. The git repo is the difference between a mind that simulates and a mind whose simulations survive.</p>
</div></section>
